ount to customers who come in openly brandishing a gun. \u000aTrent Brooks, proud owner of a Springfield handgun and barbecue joint Brook\u2019s Place, \u201cknown for its brisket and sides\u201d, chose to celebrate his state\u2019s new open carry gun law with the money off deal, which he says has led to an uptick in trade. \u000aPreviously, customers carrying a concealed weapson were only entitled to 10 per cent off. Seriously. \u000aA meme being circulated by America\u2019s Young Consservatives group claims to show \u201chow far we\u2019ve fallen from the view our Founders had of liberty and security.\u201d \u000a\u201cPutting guns in the hands of good, law-abiding citizens who will look out for each other is how we stay safe, not through suspending our freedom,\u201d they say. \u000aBut, in a country where freedoms of speech is paramount, all parties have a right of reply. We'll let you be the judge. \u000aAre you a gun owner in America and want to have your say? Email youngma@news.com.au. \u000a
